title: Jake Paul’s fiance Jutta Leerdam earns royal honour at Huis ten Bosch Palace after record breaking Olympic win
summary_full: Jutta Leerdam won gold in the 1,000m and silver in the 500m at the Milano Cortina Winter Olympics. After her success, she was named a Knight of the Order of Orange-Nassau by the Dutch royal family. The ceremony took place at Huis ten Bosch Palace. Jake Paul celebrated proudly as fans praised her achievements online.
